        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 14 at 8:22PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 815 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking slow moving showers and
thunderstorms near Appomattox National Historic Park, or near
Appomattox. These showers were nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Ponding of water on roads and flooding of poor drainage
areas.

Locations impacted include...
Appomattox...
Bent Creek...
Pamplin City...
Toga...
Appomattox National Historic Park...
Wingina...
and Hixburg.
</description>
        <instruction>Between 1.0 to 1.5 inches of rain is possible. If outdoors, consider
seeking shelter and avoiding poor drainage areas.

Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</instruction>
